title: BUbreakingSectionTwo
description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from BUbreakingSectionTwo, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: Germans Are Buying More Electric Cars, but Not Teslas
items.description: Drivers in the country, Europe’s largest car market, are avoiding vehicles from Tesla, which has seen a drop in sales in other countries as well.

items.title: Drone Attacks Are the New Front in War. Can NATO Keep Up?
items.description: Assaults in Russia and Ukraine have shown major military powers that they are unprepared for evolving forms of warfare, and need to adapt.

items.title: Germany unveils €45.8 billion in corporate tax breaks to supercharge stagnant economy
items.description: Under the plans, Germany's corporate tax rate would fall by one percent a year from 2028 to reach 10 percent, down from 15 percent.

items.title: Exclusive: Vivrelle raises $62 million to expand its service renting handbags from Prada and Chanel as part of a luxury ‘lifestyle’
items.description: The startup is part of the next generation of rental services.

items.title: This plant compound could lower your risk of heart disease and diabetes, according to new research
items.description: A new study is among the first to show the benefits of phytosterols as part of a regular diet.

items.title: At Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs Trial, Video Expert Testifies About Hotel Footage of Abuse
items.description: Later on Wednesday, a friend of Sean Combs’s former girlfriend Casandra Ventura is set to give her account of being dangled from a 17th-floor balcony.

items.title: Rails launches perps-only crypto exchange in the U.S. with $14 million in new funding to build a better FTX
items.description: Rails is backed by Sam Lessin’s Slow Ventures and cofounded by the former Grindr COO.

items.title: Campbell’s says soup sales are soaring—and that’s actually a sign the U.S. economy is in a downturn, data shows
items.description: More people are cooking at home since early 2020.

items.title: Edmund White, Pioneer of Queer Literature, Is Dead at 85
items.description: He mined his own varied catalog of sexual experiences in more than 30 books of fiction and nonfiction.

items.title: Deadly Aid Deliveries in Gaza
items.description: Israel’s troops have repeatedly shot near food distribution sites.

items.title: Trump Budget Eliminates Funding for Crucial Global Vaccination Programs
items.description: The spending proposal terminates support of health programs that, according to the proposal, “do not make Americans safer.”

items.title: Jury in El Salvador Convicts 3 Ex-Officers in 1982 Killings of Dutch Journalists
items.description: A jury convicted the former military officers for the murder of four Dutch television journalists who were covering the Salvadoran civil war.

items.title: Attack on Aid Convoy in Sudan Kills 5, U.N. Says
items.description: The delivery was supposed to be the first to arrive in the embattled city of El Fasher, the capital of North Darfur State, in more than a year.

items.title: Ayatollah Khamenei, Iran’s Supreme Leader, Calls U.S. Nuclear Deal Proposal ‘Nonsense’
items.description: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said that abandoning uranium enrichment would be against Iran’s interests.
